column5: Wow two days out on the new boat. First day we slimed it good,and today we decided to see if we could get her greased. The new boat has some magic. Terry never gets the first fish when it comes to down rigg,n lakers. That changed today. The morning did start out very slow. Lots of hooks,but no takers. Then it happen.  Terry nails a nice Simcoe laker. And it wasnt on our usual go too,s.       I was running my go to baits,and it took sometime til I finaly got one.     Lots of boats out there this morning. We stayed away from the pack and tried new waters.  Thanks again bud.  Do it again soon.
it was funsmall mouth  and lakers  off the list..now where can we find tarponlolI will try to dget a video together
